## Development

Install frontend dependencies, then run Vite and Rust together:

```sh
cd [[= project.frontend_dir]]
[[= package_manager.executable]] install
cd ..
cargo inertia dev
```

## Self-contained release

`cargo inertia build` always builds the configured frontend first, verifies its
Vite manifest, and then compiles the Rust binary that embeds the generated files:

```sh
cargo inertia build --release
```

The command prints the actual executable path reported by Cargo. If you invoke
Cargo directly instead, build the frontend first:

```sh
[[= package_manager.executable]] --dir [[= project.frontend_dir]] run build
cargo build --release
```

The release executable serves `/build` without reading `[[= project.frontend_dir]]/dist`
at runtime. Source maps are embedded when Vite emits them; decide whether production
source maps should be public in `[[= project.frontend_dir]]/vite.config.ts`.
